<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
According to International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (ICN) Articles 6.9, 6.11, 41.2, and 58.1 (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Beijing: Science Press; St. Louis: Missouri Botanical Garden Press, Vol. 20 - 21" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" refId="B9" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF [Eds], 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. X. Fu, A. G. Zhen, &amp; Y. P. Ma" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysanthemum dabieshanense" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dabieshanense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Chrysanthemum dabieshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Z.X.Fu, A.G.Zhen, &amp; Y.P.Ma, nom. nov. is proposed here as an explicit substitute for the legitimate name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fu &amp; Liu &amp; Zhen &amp; Zhu &amp; Konowalik &amp; Ma &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysanthemum vestitum subsp. var. var. latifolium" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vestitum" subSpecies="var." variety="latifolium">Chrysanthemum vestitum var. latifolium</taxonomicName>
, because the epithet 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">latifolium</emphasis>
cannot be used for the present combination because of the existence of the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysanthemum latifolium" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="latifolium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Chrysanthemum latifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Baksay, Ann. Hist. Nat. Mus. Natl. Hung. 8: 161, 1957 (online resource from https://www.tropicos.org/name/50268974). The specific epithet &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">dabieshanense</emphasis>
&quot; refers to the name of the Dabieshan (= Ta-pieh) mountain area, located at the border of the Anhui, Hubei, and Henan Provinces, where the species occurs. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. X. Fu, A. G. Zhen, &amp; Y. P. Ma" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysanthemum dabieshanense" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dabieshanense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Chrysanthemum dabieshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic and restricted to the Dabieshan Mountain area (Hubei and Anhui provinces). Therefore, we accept 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Z. X. Fu, A. G. Zhen, &amp; Y. P. Ma" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysanthemum dabieshanense" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dabieshanense">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Chrysanthemum dabieshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement name for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fu &amp; Liu &amp; Zhen &amp; Zhu &amp; Konowalik &amp; Ma &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysanthemum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysanthemum vestitum subsp. var. var. latifolium" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vestitum" subSpecies="var." variety="latifolium">Chrysanthemum vestitum var. latifolium</taxonomicName>
. A taxonomic treatment is presented.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
