<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Endemic to the Dabieshan mountain area (Anhui and Hubei Provinces, China, Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Distribution map of Chrysanthemum dabieshanense (black circles) in Anhui and Hubei provinces, China, based on the voucher specimen information." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.202.80554.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/717891" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4</figureCitation>
). It grows on shaded slopes, hills, and streamsides, at alt. 800-1600 m.
</paragraph>
